==English==
===Etymology===
French ''[[plombier]]''. See [[Plumb]]
===Noun===
'''plumber''' ([[plumbers]])
#One who works in lead (Latin: Plumbum).
#''(by extension):'' one who furnishes, fits, and repairs lead, iron, glass or plastic pipes, and other apparatus for the conveyance of water, gas, or drainage.  Originally one who did piping for waste water as distinct from a [[pipe fitter]] who dealt only with fresh water.

